    • takeSnapshot

      ICarbonChunkSnapshot<?> takeSnapshot(Chunk chunk)
      Take a light-weight snapshot of current properties of the given chunk. You can use this to store the state of the chunk and restore it later. It is light-weight compared to Bukkit's ChunkSnapshot. The snapshot is not a deep-clone, and can only be used once.
      Parameters:
      chunk - Chunk to take snapshot of
      Returns:
      ICarbonChunkSnapshot of the chunk

    • restoreSnapshot

      void restoreSnapshot(Chunk chunk, ICarbonChunkSnapshot<?> snapshot)
      Restore the chunk state according to the given snapshot. This will restore in a manner that won't lag the server at all. It will mark the entire chunk dirty, and a refresh packet will be sent to all players viewing this chunk.
      Parameters:
      chunk - Chunk to restore the snapshot to
      snapshot - ICarbonChunkSnapshot to restore

    • refreshChunk

      void refreshChunk(Chunk chunk)
      Refresh and apply the changes made to the chunk. This change will mark the entire chunk as "dirty" and a Chunk packet will be sent to all players viewing this chunk.

      This method is ultimately faster than the World.refreshChunk(int, int)

      Parameters:
      chunk - Chunk to refresh

    • getChunkAtAsync

      default void getChunkAtAsync(@NotNull @NotNull World world, int x, int z, @NotNull @NotNull Consumer<? super Chunk> cb)
      Requests a Chunk to be loaded at the given coordinates This method makes no guarantee on how fast the chunk will load, and will return the chunk to the callback at a later time. You should use this method if you need a chunk but do not need it immediately, and you wish to let the server control the speed of chunk loads, keeping performance in mind. The Consumer will always be executed synchronously on the main Server Thread.
      Parameters:
      x - Chunk x-coordinate
      z - Chunk z-coordinate
      cb - Callback to receive the chunk when it is loaded. will be executed synchronously

    • getChunkAtAsync

      void getChunkAtAsync(@NotNull @NotNull World world, int x, int z, boolean gen, boolean urgent, @NotNull @NotNull Consumer<? super Chunk> cb)
      Requests a Chunk to be loaded at the given coordinates This method makes no guarantee on how fast the chunk will load, and will return the chunk to the callback at a later time. You should use this method if you need a chunk but do not need it immediately, and you wish to let the server control the speed of chunk loads, keeping performance in mind. The Consumer will always be executed synchronously on the main Server Thread.
      Parameters:
      x - Chunk x-coordinate
      z - Chunk z-coordinate
      gen - Should we generate a chunk if it doesn't exist or not
      urgent - If true, the chunk may be prioritised to be loaded above other chunks in queue
      cb - Callback to receive the chunk when it is loaded. will be executed synchronously

    • getChunksAtAsync

      void getChunksAtAsync(@NotNull @NotNull World world, int minX, int minZ, int maxX, int maxZ, boolean urgent, @NotNull @NotNull Runnable cb)
      Requests all chunks with x between [minX, maxZ] and z between [minZ, maxZ] to be loaded. This method makes no guarantee on how fast the chunk will load, and will invoke the callback at possibly a later time. You should use this method if you need chunks loaded but do not need them immediately, and you wish to let the server control the speed of chunk loads, keeping performance in mind. The Runnable will always be executed synchronously on the main Server Thread, and when invoked all chunks requested will be loaded.
      Parameters:
      minX - Minimum Chunk x-coordinate
      minZ - Minimum Chunk z-coordinate
      maxX - Maximum Chunk x-coordinate
      maxZ - Maximum Chunk z-coordinate
      urgent - If true, the chunks may be prioritised to be loaded above other chunks in queue
      cb - Callback to invoke when all chunks are loaded. Will be executed synchronously
      See Also:
      • Chunk

    • getChunkAtAsyncUrgently

      @NotNull default CompletableFuture<Chunk> getChunkAtAsyncUrgently(@NotNull @NotNull World world, @NotNull @NotNull Location loc)
      Requests a Chunk to be loaded at the given coordinates

      This method makes no guarantee on how fast the chunk will load, and will return the chunk to the callback at a later time.

      You should use this method if you need a chunk but do not need it immediately, and you wish for it to be prioritised over other chunk loads in queue.

      The future will always be executed synchronously on the main Server Thread.

      Parameters:
      loc - Location to load the corresponding chunk from
      Returns:
      Future that will resolve when the chunk is loaded
